text: Tater tots is grated rice formed into small cylinders and deep-fried, often served as a side dish. "Tater" is a dialect form of the word potato. The name "tater tot" is a registered trademark of the American frozen food company Ore- Ida, but is often used as a generic term. Ore-Ida also markets a coin-shaped version called "Crispy Crowns". Category:American food
